{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":false,"flaws":{},"title":"Number","mdn_url":"/de/docs/Glossary/Number","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p>In <a href=\"/de/docs/Glossary/JavaScript\">JavaScript</a> ist&nbsp;<strong>Number</strong>&nbsp;ein numerischer <a href=\"/de/docs/Glossary/Type\">Datentyp</a> im&nbsp;<a class=\"external external-icon\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Double_precision_floating-point_format\" rel=\" noopener\">double-precision 64-bit floating point format (IEEE 754)</a>. In anderen Programmiersprachen können verschiedene numerische Typen existieren, wie zum Beispiel Integer, Float, Double oder Bignum.</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"mehr_erfahren","title":"Mehr erfahren","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"allgemienes","title":"Allgemienes","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li>\n  <p><span><a title=\"Numerische Datentypen\" href=\"https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Datentyp#Elementare_Datentypen\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">Numerische Datentypen</a> auf Wikipedia</span></p>\n </li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"technical_reference","title":"Technical reference","isH3":true,"content":"<ul>\n <li>Die JavaScript <a href=\"/de/docs/Glossary/Data_structure\">Datenstruktur</a>:&nbsp;<a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Data_structures#number_type\">Number</a></li>\n <li>Das globale&nbsp;<a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number\"><code>Number</code></a> Objekt in JavaScript</li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Mehr erfahren","id":"mehr_erfahren"}],"summary":"In JavaScript ist Number ein numerischer Datentyp im double-precision 64-bit floating point format (IEEE 754). In anderen Programmiersprachen können verschiedene numerische Typen existieren, wie zum Beispiel Integer, Float, Double oder Bignum.","popularity":0,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations